I feel like you have to give an ultimatum; either a pay raise to match a competitors offer (lie and say you were offered more money at a different position) or quit.
Realistically you shouldnt quit though so I would continue looking for careers while at work, preferrably one with better benefits (more 401k match, health benefits, higher pay, unlimited PTO, etc.)
A large % of people get pay raises not by staying in a company, but by stating their previous work experience and how efficiently they worked whether it be through projects or referrals.
Your employer is not your friend; they see you are doing extra work and dont want to reward you since you're already doing it at no extra pay; they don't respect you.
Bottom line is give them the ultimatum, but if you want a pay raise and they wont give you one, you will likely find it at a new job. Its much easier for companies to justify hiring VS pay raises as well, because pay raises dont necessarily change how a company works, but hiring someone new does
